  &lt;p id="RSMnyr"&gt;Teenage Engineering’s new &lt;a href="https://teenage.engineering/products/op-xy"&gt;OP-XY&lt;/a&gt; is a portable synthesizer and sequencer that looks similar to the company’s &lt;a href="https://teenage.engineering/store/op-1-field/?srsltid=AfmBOooacg__9SKptrN6z36SqsSz2iNnGPNsQvYrQey68CAe6jb1ASaq"&gt;OP–1 Field&lt;/a&gt;. But functionally it’s instead a more capable upgrade to the company’s &lt;a href="https://teenage.engineering/products/op-z"&gt;six-year-old OP-Z&lt;/a&gt;, with a stronger focus on layering sounds with various effects and a steeper $2,299 price tag.&lt;/p&gt;
