    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Vector art of the TikTok logo." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZVodkScKVxTqVABgXF35o3lud1k=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723835/STK051_TIKTOK_CVirginia_C.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="OHfva2"&gt;TikTok will let advertisers &lt;a href="https://newsroom.gettyimages.com/en/getty-images/getty-images-unlocks-premium-creative-content-for-tiktok-advertisers"&gt;pull in content from Getty Images&lt;/a&gt; when using the platform’s AI ad creation tool. With the integration, advertisers can use Getty’s licensed images and videos to make ads containing AI-generated content, including AI avatars that look like real people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="Gjx6ND"&gt;The integration will be available through &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24179971/tiktok-ads-ai-generated-avatars-creators-language-dubbing"&gt;TikTok’s Symphony Creative Studio&lt;/a&gt; — an AI-powered video generation tool &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296429/more-ai-generated-ads-are-coming-to-tiktok"&gt;that rolled out today for all advertisers&lt;/a&gt;. This tool can generate a video based on a product description, add an AI avatar to “speak” about it, and even incorporate AI-powered dubbing in different languages. Advertisers can also use the tool to generate multiple versions of an ad, as well as “remix” an existing one.&lt;/p&gt;
